✅ Car Hire Mobile Application – Requirements
1. Overview

The Car Hire Mobile App is a simple mobile application built using React Native (Expo) and JavaScript. The system allows users to view available cars, make bookings, and manage their rental experience. The backend may be provided through an API or a simple database integration.

✅ 2. Functional Requirements
2.1 User Registration & Authentication (Optional for basic version)

Users should be able to create an account using email and password.

Users should be able to log in and log out.

Users should be able to edit their profile information.

2.2 Car Listing

The system shall display a list of available cars for hire.

Each car shall include:

Car name/model

Car image

Price per day

Car type (SUV, Sedan, Van, etc.)

Basic description

2.3 Car Details Page

Users should be able to tap on a car to view:

Full description

Price breakdown

Car features (capacity, transmission, etc.)

Availability

2.4 Car Booking

Users shall be able to:

Select rental start and end dates

Confirm booking

View estimated total cost

The app shall save the booking to the database/API.

2.5 Booking Management

Users shall be able to:

View all their bookings

Cancel a booking

See booking status (pending, confirmed, completed)

2.6 Notifications (Optional for basic version)

The system may notify users when:

Booking is confirmed

Booking is canceled

A car becomes available

2.7 Payment (Optional for basic version)

The app may allow:

Mobile money simulation (e.g., M-Pesa mock)

Cash-on-delivery option

✅ 3. Non-Functional Requirements
3.1 Performance

The app should load car lists within 3 seconds.

Navigation between screens should be smooth with minimal lag.

3.2 Security

Passwords must be securely handled (if authentication is included).

User data should be protected through secure API communication.

3.3 Usability

The app should have an intuitive and visually pleasing UI.

Buttons must be easy to tap (minimum 44px height).

Text must be readable and appropriately sized.

3.4 Scalability

The app should allow for easy addition of:

More car categories

More detailed car attributes

Additional modules like payments or GPS tracking

3.5 Compatibility

The application must run on:

Android devices (primary target)

iOS devices (optional if Expo build is used)

✅ 4. Technical Requirements
4.1 Frontend

Built with React Native using Expo.

Should use:

React Navigation for routing

Context API or Redux for state management

Axios or Fetch API for backend communication

Expo Image Picker (optional for profile pictures)

4.2 Backend (Depending on your setup)

Node.js / Spring Boot / Firebase / Supabase or any backend of your choice.

REST API endpoints for:

Login

Register

Get all cars

Get single car details

Create booking

Get bookings by user

4.3 Database

SQLite / Firebase / PostgreSQL / MySQL

Must store:

User data

Car inventory

Booking records

✅ 5. Deliverables

Fully functional Expo mobile application

Car listing screen

Car details screen

Booking functionality

Booking management screen

API integration

Basic UI design